WEBVTT

00:04.612 --> 00:07.030
I thought you weren't
allowed here.

00:07.114 --> 00:08.080
I'm permitted
on school grounds

00:08.148 --> 00:09.950
as long as I'm
getting my work.

00:10.001 --> 00:11.334
Oh, I wanted to tell you
I'm available

00:11.419 --> 00:12.619
for vocal coaching
if you need any help.

00:12.670 --> 00:14.087
We need to bring our "A" game

00:14.154 --> 00:16.039
if we have any chance
of beating the Trouble Tones.

00:16.123 --> 00:17.490
Oh, we're not gonna have any
trouble with them.

00:17.542 --> 00:20.177
Not as soon as I have
Shelby Corcoran fired.

00:20.261 --> 00:21.995
She's sleeping with Puck.

00:22.046 --> 00:25.632
Look, that's a really, really
dangerous rumor

00:25.683 --> 00:27.300
to make up, okay?

00:27.351 --> 00:28.969
You're gonna ruin
her entire reputation.

00:29.020 --> 00:29.886
That's the plan.
And it's not a lie.

00:29.971 --> 00:31.388
I heard it from Puck.

00:31.472 --> 00:34.173
First of all, Puck is 18, so
what he and Shelby are doing,

00:34.225 --> 00:38.177
even though it's just wrong
and so gross, it's not illegal.

00:38.229 --> 00:39.512
So all you're doing
is you're just,

00:39.564 --> 00:40.614
you're getting her fired,

00:40.681 --> 00:42.232
which is gonna take away
her income

00:42.316 --> 00:44.534
to provide food and clothes

00:44.619 --> 00:47.120
and put a roof over her
child's tiny little blonde head.

00:47.187 --> 00:48.205
Sounds like an unfit mother.

00:48.289 --> 00:49.539
And I'll be waiting in the wings

00:49.624 --> 00:50.991
when they take Beth away
from her.

00:51.042 --> 00:51.992
Beth loves her mom.

00:52.043 --> 00:54.411
Shelby is her real mom.

00:54.495 --> 00:57.297
Look, you've done a lot
of really bad things, Quinn,

00:57.364 --> 01:00.333
but if you tell people about
this Puck-and-Shelby thing,

01:00.384 --> 01:02.201
you'll be ruining this little
girl's life,

01:02.253 --> 01:03.887
and then you'll have really
hit rock bottom.

01:11.929 --> 01:15.482
Sectionals is in our auditorium
for the first time since 1963,

01:15.549 --> 01:17.434
Too much talking,
not enough looking

01:17.518 --> 01:18.551
for songs for Sectionals.

01:18.603 --> 01:20.053
We need to do something upbeat.

01:20.104 --> 01:21.655
Mr. Shue, maybe we need
to concentrate

01:21.722 --> 01:23.907
on our performer problem
before we set a set list.

01:23.991 --> 01:25.892
I mean, at least
the Cheerios! can dance.

01:25.943 --> 01:27.944
We need star power.

01:28.029 --> 01:29.946
We need Sam Evans.

01:30.031 --> 01:31.498
Sam transferred.
His whole family moved.

01:31.565 --> 01:33.199
We don't even know where he is.

01:33.251 --> 01:34.701
He's in Kentucky.

01:34.752 --> 01:36.336
It's just across the
border from Cincinnati.

01:36.403 --> 01:38.121
It's about a four hours
from here.

01:38.205 --> 01:40.790
Even homeless people
have Facebook.

01:43.577 --> 01:45.629
Rachel and I might
as well get used

01:45.713 --> 01:48.131
to a life of barista work
and summer stock.

01:48.215 --> 01:49.599
There's no way we're
getting into NYADA now.

01:49.684 --> 01:51.250
If we don't win at Sectionals,

01:51.302 --> 01:52.969
I pretty much have nothing
to live for.

01:53.054 --> 01:56.022
New Directions! is a mess,
and we're gonna lose, Kurt,

01:56.090 --> 01:58.141
and I can't do a thing about it.

01:58.225 --> 02:00.060
Every time I open my mouth,

02:00.111 --> 02:02.929
Finn gives me these looks like,
"What does he think he's doing?"

02:02.980 --> 02:04.814
I know what I'm doing.

02:04.899 --> 02:06.366
Hey, guys!

02:06.433 --> 02:08.535
It's so crazy.
I'm sitting

02:08.602 --> 02:10.203
over there
checking out this guy

02:10.270 --> 02:11.705
and all of a sudden I'm, like,

02:11.772 --> 02:15.041
"Wait a second
I know that hair."

02:15.109 --> 02:16.960
What's up, buddy?
Haven't seen you online.

02:17.044 --> 02:18.628
Hi, Kurt.

02:18.713 --> 02:20.630
We've been really busy
with Glee Club.

02:20.715 --> 02:22.782
Practicing for Sectionals...
together.

02:22.833 --> 02:26.452
Mmm, congrats on the Warbler win
at your sectionals.

02:26.504 --> 02:28.955
We're up this week.

02:29.006 --> 02:31.725
Yeah. Well, hey, if there's one
guy that can whip New Directions

02:31.792 --> 02:34.427
into a legitimate threat,
it's Blaine Anderson, right?

02:34.478 --> 02:36.295
Right.
I need another coffee.

02:37.982 --> 02:40.517
I don't like you.

02:40.601 --> 02:42.686
Fun.
I don't like you either.

02:42.770 --> 02:45.438
I don't like the way
you talk to my boyfriend,

02:45.489 --> 02:47.490
I don't like your smirky
little meerkat face,

02:47.575 --> 02:49.776
I don't like your
obnoxious CW hair. I'm onto you.

02:49.827 --> 02:52.362
Let's get a few things straight.
Blaine's too good for you.

02:52.446 --> 02:54.147
New Directions! is a joke.

02:54.198 --> 02:55.699
And one of us has
a hard luck case

02:55.783 --> 02:57.483
of the gay-face,
and it ain't me.

02:57.535 --> 03:00.453
Odds are by the end of the
school year, I'll have Blaine

03:00.504 --> 03:02.339
and a nationals trophy,
and you'll have khakis

03:02.423 --> 03:04.323
and a Lima Bean apron
and that gay face.

03:04.375 --> 03:05.759
You smell like Craig's List.

03:05.826 --> 03:08.178
What are you guys
talking about?

03:08.262 --> 03:10.130
Duh, the next time we're all
going out drinking, killer!

03:10.181 --> 03:11.715
Uh-oh.
Well, I gotta run.

03:11.799 --> 03:16.019
But you take care of that
Warbler, Kurt.

03:21.559 --> 03:22.726
Wait. This can't be
the right place.

03:22.810 --> 03:25.145
Sam works in a bar?

03:25.196 --> 03:26.980
Well, there just aren't
a lot of theaters in
Northern Kentucky,

03:27.031 --> 03:28.481
so theatre groups
just have

03:28.532 --> 03:29.949
to perform in whatever
space they can find.

03:30.017 --> 03:32.318
There's a lot of ladies here--
like, older ladies.

03:32.370 --> 03:34.738
Finn, it's no secret
that dinner theater appeals

03:34.822 --> 03:35.989
to elderly women.

03:36.040 --> 03:38.074
Good afternoon, ladies!

03:38.159 --> 03:41.161
<i>Are you ready to meet
the men of Stallionz?</i>

03:41.212 --> 03:45.999
Then please welcome
to the stage-- Cobra!

03:46.050 --> 03:48.134
<i>I didn't know Backdraft was
a musical.</i>

03:48.202 --> 03:52.305
Someone get the door,
'cause here comes Mr. Package.

03:55.393 --> 03:56.726
Oh, God, no.

03:56.811 --> 03:59.479
And ladies, let's give

03:59.546 --> 04:02.816
a warm
welcome to White Chocolate!

04:04.000 --> 04:10.074
-= www.OpenSubtitles.org =-

04:13.694 --> 04:17.414
♪ ♪

04:17.498 --> 04:19.565
That's not an image I can
ever get out of my mind.

04:19.617 --> 04:20.565
Give me a dollar.

04:20.618 --> 04:21.951
What?
Just give me a dollar.

04:28.242 --> 04:30.293
Rach-Rachel...

04:30.377 --> 04:32.378
I tried getting a real job.

04:32.430 --> 04:34.431
DQ was great and I got
two free Blizzards a day,

04:34.515 --> 04:37.767
but it paid just over
minimum wage. Thanks.

04:37.852 --> 04:39.853
You know how much
I made this afternoon?

04:39.920 --> 04:42.689
60 bucks.

04:42.756 --> 04:45.892
$61... in 15 minutes.

04:45.943 --> 04:48.445
Am I ashamed I work here?
Yeah, I'm ashamed.

04:48.529 --> 04:50.980
My dad got a job working
construction to pay the rent,

04:51.065 --> 04:52.398
but when my brother needs
a new pair of shoes

04:52.450 --> 04:55.652
or the TV busts,
these abs pay for it.

04:55.736 --> 04:57.620
Your parents don't know
that you work here?

04:57.705 --> 04:59.572
No, they just think
the DQ pays really well.

05:00.624 --> 05:01.624
I'm good at this.

05:01.709 --> 05:02.859
You're good at it
because you have

05:02.927 --> 05:03.910
that a boy-next-door
innocence

05:03.961 --> 05:04.661
that makes you
approachable, okay?

05:04.745 --> 05:06.129
You're good at it for all

05:06.213 --> 05:08.498
the reasons that you
shouldn't be doing it.

05:08.582 --> 05:12.552
Come back to McKinley, Sam.
We need you for Sectionals.

05:12.620 --> 05:13.803
Tell me you don't want it.

05:13.888 --> 05:16.089
Dude, you're young,
you got so much potential.

05:16.140 --> 05:18.842
Working re is, like,
throwing your life away.

05:18.926 --> 05:22.979
Okay, I want it... but
my dad will never let me.

05:23.063 --> 05:24.998
Don't know till you ask.

05:25.065 --> 05:26.850
Here we go.

05:31.338 --> 05:34.240
Dad, Mom, what
I'm trying to say

05:34.308 --> 05:36.442
is I want to go back
to Ohio with them.

05:36.494 --> 05:37.861
They need me to compete at
Sectionals this weekend.

05:37.945 --> 05:39.496
And he could stay at one
of our houses,

05:39.580 --> 05:41.164
so it wouldn't be
like he was homeless.

05:41.248 --> 05:42.499
Not that there isn't

05:42.583 --> 05:45.518
a quiet dignity in that
or anything.

05:45.586 --> 05:48.654
You think you two could
go in the other room,

05:48.706 --> 05:50.323
make yourselves
busy, please?

05:50.391 --> 05:52.609
Yeah, totally-- I'm really
good at looking busy.

05:55.629 --> 05:58.765
Son...

05:58.832 --> 06:00.650
we've had a really tough year,

06:00.718 --> 06:02.068
but now we've back
on our feet.

06:03.604 --> 06:06.739
You had to become
a man much sooner

06:06.807 --> 06:08.775
than other kids your age.

06:08.842 --> 06:11.311
I'm-I'm proud of
what we've all done.

06:11.378 --> 06:12.879
It's just that...

06:12.947 --> 06:16.533
I miss being a teenager.

06:17.785 --> 06:19.986
Hey-hey-hey-hey...

06:20.037 --> 06:23.406
Mom, please don't...
Look, if you cry, I won't go.

06:23.490 --> 06:26.876
I'm just crying because...

06:26.961 --> 06:28.461
it just makes me so sad

06:28.528 --> 06:30.964
to think of not seeing
your face every day.

06:31.031 --> 06:33.049
Though I don't
understand why

06:33.133 --> 06:35.468
the Dairy Queen makes you put
that glitter all over it.

06:35.535 --> 06:37.670
This gonna make you happy?

06:37.721 --> 06:39.722
You have no idea.

06:42.893 --> 06:43.893
Come on.

06:47.714 --> 06:49.649
Are we sure yet which band
members are joining us?

06:49.716 --> 06:51.601
Well, it looks like
"Floppy Hair Bass Dude,"

06:51.685 --> 06:53.736
"Chapped Lips McGee,"
and "Johnny Tromboner."

06:53.821 --> 06:55.355
God, we're screwed.
No, we're not.

06:55.406 --> 06:57.556
I know for a fact
that we're winning.

06:57.608 --> 06:58.608
Hey, great news,
everybody.

06:58.692 --> 06:59.659
Sectionals is going to be

06:59.726 --> 07:01.194
a challenge, but we have a--

07:01.245 --> 07:04.330
Mr. Shue, we all appreciate
your endless supply

07:04.398 --> 07:07.617
of affirmations, but all
the sparkling cider in the world

07:07.701 --> 07:09.369
<i>can't deny the fact
that the Titanic has hit</i>

07:09.420 --> 07:11.120
the iceberg and now
we're on a sinking ship.

07:11.205 --> 07:13.572
Not if I can help it.

07:17.011 --> 07:18.094
Hey.
Hi!

07:18.178 --> 07:19.929
Come here!

07:21.632 --> 07:24.250
I wouldn't be here if it wasn't
for Finn and Rachel.

07:24.301 --> 07:27.186
I sort of lost my way, but...

07:27.254 --> 07:29.255
true friends help you
find your way back.

07:29.306 --> 07:31.641
Let's hear it
for Sam Evans!

07:33.310 --> 07:34.861
All right, enough
of the sentimental stuff.

07:34.928 --> 07:36.646
It's time y'all get
a little country

07:36.730 --> 07:38.147
back in this joint! Oh!

07:39.033 --> 07:40.033
Cheers!

07:40.100 --> 07:42.485
Two, one, two, three.

07:42.569 --> 07:45.371
(Toby Keith's "Red Solo Cup"
begins)

07:47.741 --> 07:52.278
♪ Now a red Solo cup is the best
receptacle for barbecues ♪

07:52.329 --> 07:54.664
♪ Tailgates,
fairs and festivals ♪

07:54.748 --> 07:57.000
♪ And you, sir, do not have
a pair of testicles ♪

07:57.084 --> 07:59.836
♪ If you prefer drinking
from glass ♪

07:59.920 --> 08:02.972
♪ Hey, a red Solo cup is
cheap and disposable ♪

08:03.057 --> 08:05.642
♪ And in 14 years,
they are decomposable ♪

08:05.726 --> 08:08.895
♪ And unlike my home,
they are not foreclosable ♪

08:08.962 --> 08:11.964
♪ Freddie Mac can
kiss my ass! Ooh! ♪

08:12.016 --> 08:16.736
♪ Red Solo cup, uh-huh,
I fill you up ♪

08:16.803 --> 08:19.989
<i>♪ Let's have a party ♪
♪ Let's have a party ♪</i>

08:20.074 --> 08:21.974
♪ Let's have a party ♪

08:22.026 --> 08:26.362
♪ I love you, red Solo cup ♪

08:26.447 --> 08:29.782
♪ I lift you up,
proceed to party ♪

08:29.833 --> 08:31.817
♪ Proceed to party ♪

08:31.869 --> 08:34.671
♪ Proceed to party ♪
♪ Proceed to party ♪

08:34.755 --> 08:38.006
♪ Now, I seen you in blue
and I've seen you in yellow ♪

08:38.092 --> 08:40.826
♪ But only you, Red,
will do for this fellow ♪

08:40.878 --> 08:44.047
♪ 'Cause you are the Abbot
unto my Costello ♪

08:44.131 --> 08:45.998
♪ And you are the fruit
to my loom ♪

08:46.050 --> 08:50.053
♪ Red Solo cup, you're more
than just plastic ♪

08:50.137 --> 08:52.171
♪ You're more than amazing,
you're more than fantastic ♪

08:52.222 --> 08:55.358
♪ Believe me when I'm not
the least bit sarcastic ♪

08:55.442 --> 08:58.728
♪ When I look at you
and say... ♪

08:58.812 --> 09:02.365
Red solo cup,
you're not just a cup.

09:02.449 --> 09:03.783
God, no!

09:03.850 --> 09:05.684
You're my...

09:05.736 --> 09:06.819
Friend?

09:06.870 --> 09:07.904
You're my friend.

09:09.356 --> 09:11.240
Thank you for being my friend,
red Solo cup.

09:11.325 --> 09:13.192
Aw...

09:13.243 --> 09:17.830
♪ Red Solo cup, I fill you up ♪

09:17.881 --> 09:20.917
♪ Let's have a party ♪
♪ Have a party ♪

09:21.001 --> 09:23.753
♪ Let's have a party ♪
♪ Let's have
a party ♪

09:23.837 --> 09:27.640
♪ I love you, red Solo cup ♪
♪ Red Solo ♪

09:27.707 --> 09:29.258
♪ I fill you up ♪

09:29.343 --> 09:30.543
♪ Let's have a party ♪

09:30.594 --> 09:31.844
♪ Let's have a party ♪

09:31.895 --> 09:35.881
♪ Let's have a party,
yeah-eah! ♪

09:37.684 --> 09:38.568
<i>♪ Solo cup ♪</i>

09:38.652 --> 09:39.602
♪ Do-do ♪

09:39.686 --> 09:40.770
<i>♪ Solo cup ♪</i>

09:40.854 --> 09:42.488
♪ Oh, do-do ♪

09:42.556 --> 09:45.491
<i>♪ Solo cup ♪
♪ Doo-dee-da-ba ♪</i>

09:45.559 --> 09:49.195
♪ Hmm-hmm-mm. ♪

09:54.785 --> 09:56.619
Corn dogs!

09:56.703 --> 10:00.039
I just heard the news that
Trouty Mouth is back in town.

10:00.090 --> 10:01.841
I've been keeping
a notebook, just in case

10:01.908 --> 10:02.925
this day ever came.

10:03.010 --> 10:05.261
"Welcome back, Lisa Rinna.

10:05.345 --> 10:07.680
"I've missed you so much since
your family packed their bags,

10:07.747 --> 10:09.215
"loaded them in your mouth,
and skipped town.

10:09.266 --> 10:12.018
"I can't tell you how
many times I've wanted

10:12.085 --> 10:13.686
"to enjoy a crisp pickle,
but couldn't find anyone

10:13.753 --> 10:15.104
"to suck the lid off the jar.

10:15.189 --> 10:17.089
"I assume you've been
working as a baby-polisher,

10:17.141 --> 10:19.776
"where young mothers place their
infants' heads in your mouth to

10:19.860 --> 10:21.861
"get back that newborn shine.

10:21.928 --> 10:23.029
"So glad you're back.

10:23.096 --> 10:24.614
"I haven't seen
a smile that big

10:24.698 --> 10:26.983
"since a Claymation
Abominable Snowman got

10:27.067 --> 10:29.202
"his teeth pulled by
that little gay elf dentist.

10:29.269 --> 10:30.870
Love, Santana."

10:30.937 --> 10:32.872
I missed you, too, Santana.

10:32.939 --> 10:34.073
Oh, my God.

10:41.715 --> 10:43.616
Hey, Sam, wait up.

10:44.968 --> 10:46.118
I'm sure you've heard

10:46.170 --> 10:47.637
that Mercedes has
a new boyfriend.

10:47.721 --> 10:50.289
He's got a full scholarship
to Ohio State.

10:50.340 --> 10:51.507
Nice to see you,
too, Quinn.

10:51.592 --> 10:52.558
No, no, it's a good thing.

10:52.626 --> 10:54.293
See, I'm free,
you're free.

10:54.344 --> 10:56.012
And I'm sure that you've noticed
that I'm supermodel thin

10:56.096 --> 10:58.147
now that my thyroid is
under control.

10:58.232 --> 11:00.349
What do you want, Quinn?

11:00.434 --> 11:03.236
Look, last year
I didn't appreciate you.

11:03.303 --> 11:05.021
But we're
perfect together.

11:05.105 --> 11:06.805
Quinn...
I'm gonna get Beth back.

11:06.857 --> 11:09.659
And-And you'd be perfect
to help raise her.

11:09.726 --> 11:11.244
You're so good with kids.

11:11.311 --> 11:12.278
What is so funny?

11:12.329 --> 11:13.913
Quinn, you've got

11:13.980 --> 11:15.281
what I call "rich
white girl problems."

11:15.332 --> 11:17.149
It's a tough world
out there, I know.

11:17.201 --> 11:18.251
I've been through it.

11:18.318 --> 11:22.255
You only get one senior year.

11:22.322 --> 11:23.623
Enjoy it.

11:25.709 --> 11:28.177
You know that song "Jack and
Diane" by John Mellencamp?

11:28.262 --> 11:29.846
Please don't sing.
My favorite lyric

11:29.930 --> 11:31.830
is this one:

11:31.882 --> 11:35.635
"Hold on to 16 as
long as you can."

11:50.399 --> 11:51.933
with the applications?
Deadlines are this week.

11:51.984 --> 11:54.969
Tina, I already applied
to Stanford.

11:55.020 --> 11:55.987
Pre-med.

11:58.240 --> 12:00.408
But you don't want to be a
doctor, you want to be a dancer.

12:00.475 --> 12:02.860
Not if it means ripping
my family apart.

12:02.945 --> 12:04.495
My dad hasn't said
one word to me

12:04.580 --> 12:06.164
<i>or my mom since
West Side Story.</i>

12:06.248 --> 12:07.415
I'll dance in my free time.

12:07.482 --> 12:09.000
Everyone's happy.

12:09.084 --> 12:11.819
Except for you.
Mike, your dad needs to

12:11.870 --> 12:13.254
understand that dancing
is your passion,

12:13.321 --> 12:14.505
not some extracurricular.

12:14.590 --> 12:15.990
I miss him, Tina.

12:16.041 --> 12:18.009
I know.
But you have one life, Mike.

12:18.093 --> 12:20.828
One chance to get it right.

12:20.879 --> 12:22.046
Don't be a coward.

12:22.131 --> 12:23.097
Don't call me that.

12:23.165 --> 12:24.765
You won't make it as a dancer

12:24.833 --> 12:27.101
if you're not 100% committed.

12:30.305 --> 12:31.689
So maybe your dad's right.

12:31.773 --> 12:33.674
Maybe you should be a doctor.

12:33.725 --> 12:36.343
Or maybe he's right,
and we shouldn't be together.

12:39.982 --> 12:41.232
...six, seven, eight.

12:41.316 --> 12:42.617
Bum-bum-bum.

12:42.684 --> 12:43.851
Step and hit.

12:43.902 --> 12:45.036
Come on!
To the beat!

12:45.120 --> 12:46.537
What does it even
matter, anyway?

12:46.622 --> 12:47.788
It's not like we have
a chance of winning.

12:47.856 --> 12:48.873
Not without the girls.

12:48.957 --> 12:51.209
Sir, girls smell
better than ham

12:51.293 --> 12:52.910
and when they're dancing
and bouncing around,

12:52.995 --> 12:53.995
you can't help but watch them.

12:54.046 --> 12:55.880
Well, that's it then.

12:55.964 --> 12:57.798
We'll take what's most appealing
about us as a group,

12:57.866 --> 12:59.584
and we'll use it
to our advantage.

12:59.668 --> 13:02.470
Yeah, how about, you know,
something like, um...

13:02.537 --> 13:04.255
something like that?

13:04.339 --> 13:05.539
Cute!
I like the spin,
I like the spin.

13:05.591 --> 13:06.373
Try it again.

13:06.425 --> 13:07.558
Yeah.

13:07.643 --> 13:08.509
God, okay, stop, stop.

13:08.560 --> 13:09.927
Look, Blaine,

13:10.012 --> 13:12.563
this... is totally boy band.

13:12.648 --> 13:15.683
What we need
to sell here is sex.

13:15.734 --> 13:17.101
What the hell is that?

13:17.186 --> 13:18.319
That's a, it's a body roll.

13:18.386 --> 13:19.437
It's not a body roll.

13:19.521 --> 13:22.389
That is sex.

13:25.393 --> 13:27.278
Man's not wrong.

13:27.362 --> 13:29.947
I got light tingles where
it's only 50/50 for tingling.

13:30.032 --> 13:31.199
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Sam, that's awesome.

13:31.250 --> 13:32.617
That's exactly what we need.

13:32.701 --> 13:34.252
No, that's not,
that's not what we need.

13:34.336 --> 13:37.571
We don't have to
resort to... that.

13:37.623 --> 13:39.240
It's cheap.

13:39.291 --> 13:40.208
You know, it's selling out.

13:40.259 --> 13:41.626
I came back here to win.

13:41.710 --> 13:44.178
When you're desperate,
sometimes you got to,

13:44.246 --> 13:45.763
you know, use your assets
and do what you got to do

13:45.847 --> 13:46.747
to get back that advantage.

13:46.798 --> 13:49.433
This is the advantage.

13:49.518 --> 13:50.801
Of course that's what you think;
you have to

13:50.886 --> 13:52.053
think that
in order to sleep at night.

13:52.104 --> 13:53.888
What the hell does that mean?

13:53.939 --> 13:55.640
It means that
I'm not for sale.

13:55.724 --> 13:57.358
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

13:57.425 --> 13:59.310
Hey.

13:59.394 --> 14:00.561
Forget it.

14:08.270 --> 14:09.203
Is that Sam's face?

14:09.271 --> 14:11.205
Yep. Yours, too.

14:12.624 --> 14:14.542
Don't act so surprised.

14:14.609 --> 14:17.128
After getting bullied so much,
I took up boxing.

14:17.212 --> 14:18.829
I also started the Dalton
branch of Fight Club,

14:18.914 --> 14:24.252
which I obviously
can't talk about!

14:24.303 --> 14:26.137
What is your problem
with me, anyway?!

14:26.221 --> 14:28.673
Ever since I got here, you've
given me nothing but crap.

14:31.126 --> 14:33.678
Honestly, dude,
I was kind of jealous.

14:33.762 --> 14:36.397
I felt threatened.

14:36.464 --> 14:39.433
Your talent kind of
freaked me out,

14:39.484 --> 14:41.602
made me question whether or not
I was good enough.

14:41.653 --> 14:45.239
Look, Blaine, I'm sorry.

14:45.307 --> 14:48.426
Uh, I've been acting
like a jackass to you.

14:48.493 --> 14:51.195
With Rachel gone,
you're the most

14:51.280 --> 14:53.648
talented, well-rounded member
of this team.

14:53.715 --> 14:56.417
And now more than ever,
we need to be on the same page.

14:56.485 --> 14:58.586
United.

15:00.372 --> 15:02.623
Tell me what you need me to do.

15:02.674 --> 15:04.258
We have an opportunity.

15:04.326 --> 15:06.294
An opportunity to be remembered
at this school

15:06.345 --> 15:08.763
for the rest of our lives
for doing the impossible.

15:08.830 --> 15:12.350
But it all starts right here,
with you and me.

15:12.434 --> 15:15.469
I just want to be able to look
across that stage at you

15:15.520 --> 15:20.057
and know that we did
everything we could.

15:20.142 --> 15:22.059
No regrets.

15:29.284 --> 15:30.985
Let's get back to work.

15:32.687 --> 15:33.704
All right.

15:36.124 --> 15:37.575
What are you doing?

15:37.659 --> 15:39.193
Holding your hand.

15:39.244 --> 15:40.077
Don't.

15:40.162 --> 15:41.078
Sam, look, I...

15:41.163 --> 15:42.630
I heard about your boyfriend.

15:42.697 --> 15:45.366
Then you heard he's
built like a bulldozer.

15:48.587 --> 15:50.504
We had a summer fling.
It was more than that.

15:50.555 --> 15:53.424
I'll always have a special place
in my heart for you,

15:53.508 --> 15:56.427
but... I've moved on.

15:56.511 --> 15:58.512
And you need to do the same.

16:01.716 --> 16:04.235
I don't care how big
or bad your boyfriend is.

16:04.319 --> 16:06.070
I'm gonna fight
to get you back.

16:19.138 --> 16:20.639
<i>What's this?
A bootleg of
West Side Story.</i>

16:20.723 --> 16:22.641
Starring your son.

16:22.725 --> 16:25.026
You missed
the performance,

16:25.094 --> 16:27.579
but I thought you should see how
truly incredible Mike was in it.

16:27.647 --> 16:29.364
Go. Take that with you.

16:29.432 --> 16:30.365
Are you sure?

16:30.433 --> 16:32.033
'Cause if you saw it,

16:32.101 --> 16:34.736
then maybe you'd realize
that Mike's throwing

16:34.787 --> 16:38.573
everything he loves away
just to please you.

16:38.624 --> 16:40.942
And if you don't make it right,
he's going to spend

16:40.993 --> 16:42.828
the rest of his life
doing something he hates,

16:42.912 --> 16:44.546
dying inside.

16:44.613 --> 16:46.281
Tina...

16:46.332 --> 16:48.250
sit.

16:48.301 --> 16:49.334
Please.

16:54.340 --> 16:56.224
You want to be a performer, too?

16:57.677 --> 16:59.428
And your parents support this?

16:59.479 --> 17:00.679
They love me.

17:00.763 --> 17:01.796
They love you,

17:01.848 --> 17:02.848
but they're not honest with you.

17:02.932 --> 17:03.849
And you children,

17:03.916 --> 17:06.435
you think you know everything,

17:06.486 --> 17:08.904
but this path
you've chosen, Tina,

17:08.971 --> 17:10.704
